The **canonical "what"** — the authoritative functional and non-functional requirements. Every
requirement has a **stable ID**, is **testable**, is **prioritized** (MoSCoW), and **traces** to a
BRD goal (and, where relevant, a research finding). IDs are forever: supersede, never renumber.

> The one test for every requirement: *"How would I write a test that proves this is met?"* If you
> can't answer in one sentence, it's not a requirement yet — rewrite it. See
> `requirements-engineering`.

