## 3. Functional requirements

Each is independent, testable, single-behavior, and includes its **failure behavior**. Tag priority
**Must / Should / Could / Won't**.

| ID | Requirement | Priority | Traces to | Failure behavior |
|----|-------------|----------|-----------|------------------|
| FR-1 | <The system MUST …> | Must | BR-1 | <what happens on bad input / dependency down / limit hit> |
| FR-2 | <The system SHOULD …> | Should | BR-1, finding C2 | <…> |
| FR-3 | <…> | Could | BR-2 | <…> |

<For requirements that need elaboration — multi-step flows, edge cases — write the detail in
[`frd.md`](./frd.md) and reference it here (e.g., "FR-7 — detailed flow in frd.md §3"). Don't inline
the whole flow.>

## 4. Non-functional requirements

Numbers and conditions, not adjectives. Cover the relevant "-ilities" and explicitly mark any that
are **not a concern for v1** with a reason.

| ID | Category | Requirement (measurable) | Priority | Traces to |
|----|----------|--------------------------|----------|-----------|
| NFR-1 | Performance | <e.g. p95 read latency < 200 ms at 500 rps> | Must | BR-2 |
| NFR-2 | Reliability | <e.g. 99.9% monthly availability of the API> | Must | finding §6 |
| NFR-3 | Security | <e.g. all PII encrypted at rest; auth on every endpoint> | Must | BR-1 |
| NFR-4 | Usability | <e.g. new user completes first <task> in < N steps> | Should | finding C1 |
| NFR-5 | Operability | <e.g. structured logs + one golden-signal dashboard> | Should | — |
| — | Portability | <not a concern for v1 because <reason>> | Won't | — |

